arts.ttl: France/Iceland – The French team announced without PSG players
arts.sum: This Tuesday, the French national team will play a 2026 World Cup qualifying match against Iceland at 8:45 PM at the Parc des Princes. Three Paris Saint-Germain players, all French, are involved: Lucas Chevalier, Lucas Hernandez, and Bradley Barcola.
